<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A wood or plastic <a title="Wedge" href="Wedge">wedge</a> used in the <a title="Delivery Pile" href="Delivery_Pile">delivery pile</a> of a sheetfed printing press (especially that used in <a title="Offset Lithography" href="Offset_Lithography">offset lithography</a>) at the beginning of a pressrun. Two or more wedges are placed on the bottom of the delivery pile to support the back edge of the sheets and counteract the effects of <a title="Tail-End Hook" href="Tail-End_Hook">tail-end hook</a>, a deleterious curl at the back end of a press sheet. (See <a title="Delivery Section" href="Delivery_Section">Delivery Section</a>.) 
</p>
